This paper deals with privacy and security issues related to Tor and hidden services, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves data collection and analysis, which falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its findings for cybercrime and cybersecurity, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CY) sub-category.
